(Corrects spelling of FSC commissioner’s name in first
paragraph.)  South Korea ’s household debt is at a
broadly manageable level, Lee Suk Joon, the commissioner of the
nation’s Financial Services Commission, said.  The pace of growth in home debt is a concern, Lee told
reporters today in  Seoul .  To contact the reporter on this story:
